{"id":"2007.01982","submitter":"Nicholas Vlamis","authors":"Tarik Aougab, Priyam Patel, and Nicholas G. Vlamis","title":"Isometry groups of infinite-genus hyperbolic surfaces","comments":"49 pages, 5 figures. v2: incorporates referee's comments, final\n  version, accepted for publication","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.GT math.CV math.GR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Given a 2-manifold, a fundamental question to ask is which groups can be\nrealized as the isometry group of a Riemannan metric of constant curvature on\nthe manifold. In this paper, we give a nearly complete classification of such\ngroups for infinite-genus 2-manifolds with no planar ends. Surprisingly, we\nshow there is an uncountable class of such 2-manifolds where every countable\ngroup can be realized as an isometry group (namely, those with self-similar end\nspaces). We apply this result to obtain obstructions to standard group\ntheoretic properties for the groups of homeomorphisms, diffeomorphisms, and the\nmapping class groups of such 2-manifolds. For example, none of these groups\nsatisfy the Tits Alternative; are coherent; are linear; are cyclically or\nlinearly orderable; or are residually finite. As a second application, we give\nan algebraic rigidity result for mapping class groups.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 4 Jul 2020 01:37:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 9 Mar 2021 15:29:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-10"}
